```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_deduped_returns.sql
-- Pick one approved return per item (latest return_id per item)
WITH source AS (
    SELECT
        return_id,
        item_id,
        return_date,
        reason,
        status,
        ROW_NUMBER() OVER (
            PARTITION BY item_id
            ORDER BY return_id DESC
        ) AS row_num
    FROM {{ ref('stg_returns') }}
    WHERE status = 'approved'
)
SELECT
    item_id,
    return_id,
    return_date,
    reason
FROM source
WHERE row_num = 1
```

```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_order_items_with_returns.sql
-- Join order items with returns to identify returned items
WITH order_items AS (
    SELECT
        item_id,
        order_id,
        product_id,
        quantity,
        unit_price
    FROM {{ ref('stg_order_items') }}
)
SELECT
    oi.item_id,
    oi.product_id,
    CASE WHEN dr.item_id IS NOT NULL THEN 1 ELSE 0 END AS is_returned
FROM order_items oi
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_deduped_returns') }} dr
    ON dr.item_id = oi.item_id
```

```sql
-- models/intermediate/int_products_with_categories.sql
-- Join products with categories, handling missing category values
WITH products AS (
    SELECT
        product_id,
        name,
        category_id
    FROM {{ ref('stg_products') }}
)
SELECT
    p.product_id,
    p.name,
    COALESCE(c.category_id, -1) AS category_id,
    COALESCE(c.name, '(unknown)') AS category_name
FROM products p
LEFT JOIN {{ ref('stg_categories') }} c
    ON c.category_id = p.category_id
```

-- models/mart/fct_return_rate_by_category.sql
-- Calculate product return rates by category
WITH items_with_returns AS (
    SELECT
        oiwr.product_id,
        oiwr.is_returned
    FROM {{ ref('int_order_items_with_returns') }} oiwr
),
items_with_categories AS (
    SELECT
        iwc.category_name,
        iwc.product_id,
        ir.is_returned
    FROM items_with_returns ir
    LEFT JOIN {{ ref('int_products_with_categories') }} iwc
        ON iwc.product_id = ir.product_id
)
SELECT
    category_name,
    COUNT(*) AS total_items_sold,
    SUM(is_returned) AS total_items_returned,
    ROUND(SUM(is_returned)::NUMERIC / COUNT(*), 4) AS return_rate
FROM items_with_categories
GROUP BY category_name
ORDER BY category_name
